To use TensorFlow and Hugging Face Transformers libraries in your WordPress website page, you can follow these steps:

1. Install the libraries on your server: You can install TensorFlow and Hugging Face Transformers libraries on your server using pip. Log in to your server via SSH and run the following commands:
```
pip install tensorflow
pip install transformers
```
Make sure that you have the necessary permissions to install packages on the server.

1. Load the libraries in your WordPress page: You can load the libraries in your WordPress page using the wp\_enqueue\_script() function. In the header.php file of your WordPress theme, add the following code:
```php
<?php
function load_custom_scripts() {
    wp_enqueue_script('tensorflow', 'https://unpkg.com/@tensorflow/tfjs@3.12.0/dist/tf.min.js', array(), '3.12.0', false);
    wp_enqueue_script('transformers', 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/tokenizers@0.10.3/dist/tokenizers.min.js', array(), '0.10.3', false);
}
add_action('wp_enqueue_scripts', 'load_custom_scripts');
?>
```
This code will load the TensorFlow and Hugging Face Transformers libraries in your WordPress page.

1. Use the libraries in your JavaScript code: Once the libraries are loaded, you can use them in your JavaScript code. For example, you can use the following code to load the T5 model from Hugging Face Transformers and paraphrase the input text:
```javascript
const model = await transformers.T5ForConditionalGeneration.fromPretrained('t5-base');
const tokenizer = await transformers.AutoTokenizer.fromPretrained('t5-base');
const inputText = 'This is the input text to be paraphrased.';
const inputs = tokenizer.encode(inputText);
const inputIds = tf.tensor([inputs.input_ids]);
const outputs = await model.generate(inputIds, { max_length: 50 });
const paraphrasedText = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0].toArray());
console.log(paraphrasedText);
```
Note that the above code is just an example and you may need to modify it to fit your specific use case. Also, make sure to test your code thoroughly before deploying it to production.
